## ğŸ—ï¸ HTML Elements Used

### 1. Structural Elements

* `<!DOCTYPE html>` â†’ Defines HTML5 document type.
* `<html>` â†’ Root element of the page.
* `<head>` â†’ Holds metadata, stylesheets, and scripts.
* `<body>` â†’ Contains all visible webpage content.
* `<div>` â†’ Used extensively as **containers** for grouping and styling content.

### 2. Head & Linking

* `<link>` â†’ Imports external CSS (Bootstrap & custom stylesheet).
* `<script>` â†’ Loads JavaScript files (Bootstrap JS, jQuery, custom scripts).
* `<title>` â†’ (Optional) Sets the title of the web page.

### 3. Text Content

* `<h1>` â†’ Main headings (e.g., "Tourism", "Favourite Places", "Detailed View").
* `<p>` â†’ Paragraph text (descriptions of tourist places).

### 4. Interactive Elements

* `<button>` â†’ Used for navigation (Get Started, Back buttons, etc.).
* `onclick` attribute â†’ Calls JavaScript functions to switch sections (`display('sectionid')`).

### 5. Images

* `<img>` â†’ Displays place images and carousel slides with `src`, `alt`, and `class` attributes.

### 6. Bootstrap Components

* `<div class="carousel ...">` â†’ Bootstrap **carousel (slideshow)** component.
* `<ol>` & `<li>` â†’ Indicators for carousel navigation.
* `<a>` â†’ Carousel navigation controls (Next, Previous).
* `<span>` â†’ Icons for carousel controls.

