## ğŸ¨ CSS Properties Used

### 1. Background Styling

* `background-image` â†’ Adds background images (`ocean.jpg`, `towerbg.png`, `seabg.png`).
* `background-size: cover;` â†’ Ensures the image covers the entire container.
* `background-color` â†’ Sets background color (used for cards and buttons).

### 2. Box Model

* `min-height`, `height`, `width` â†’ Controls element dimensions.
* `margin` â†’ Creates space around elements.
* `padding` â†’ Creates space inside elements.
* `border-radius` â†’ Rounds the corners of cards and buttons.
* `border-width` â†’ Removes or customizes borders (used on buttons).

### 3. Typography

* `font-family: "Roboto";` â†’ Sets the text font.
* `font-size` â†’ Defines text size (50px for headings, 18px for details, etc.).
* `font-weight` â†’ Makes text bold (e.g., headings).
* `color` â†’ Sets text color (white/black).
* `text-align` â†’ Aligns text (`center`, `start`, `justify`).

### 4. Flexbox (Bootstrap + Custom)

* `display: flex;` (`d-flex`) â†’ Enables flexible box layout.
* `flex-direction: column` / `row` â†’ Defines arrangement direction.
* `justify-content: end` â†’ Aligns items horizontally or vertically.

### 5. Image Styling

* `height`, `width` â†’ Adjust image dimensions.
* `padding` â†’ Adds spacing inside image containers.

### 6. Button Styling

* `color` â†’ Sets text color on buttons (white).
* `background-color: #25b1cc;` â†’ Custom button background (blue).
* `width`, `height` â†’ Defines button size.
* `border-radius: 20px;` â†’ Rounded button edges.
* `font-size: medium;` â†’ Adjusts button text size.

